    <Ritual>
        <Nerangs id="ritualNerangs">
            <ab>Y27.9 (mss. 40, 88, 400, 410):</ab>
            <ab class="ab_indent">
                <em>yaθā ahū vairiiō</em> čahār guftan pad ān ī fradom pad <em>š́iiaōθananąm</em> zōhr andar hōm pālā kunišn pad <em>xšaϑrəmcā</em> bē afšārišn pad ān ī dudīgar ud sidīgar ud čahārom ham ēdōn bē afšārišn</ab>
            <ab class="ab_indent">
                "He should recite the <em>yaθā ahū vairiiō</em> four times. During the first one, at <em>š́iiaōθananąm</em> he has to pour the <em>zōhr</em> into the <em>hōm-pālā</em>. At <em>xšaϑrəmcā</em>, he has to squeeze (the <em>hōm</em> and <em>urwarām</em>). During the second, third and fourth (<em>yaθā ahū vairiiō</em>),
                he has to press in the same way."</ab>
        </Nerangs>
        
        <Quotations id="ritualQuotations">
    <ab>Cf. N28.47f:</ab>
            <ab class="ab_indent">
                pad ān čahār yatāhūwēryō pad <em>š́iiaoθananąm</em> ī fradom be wardēnišn</ab> 
            <ab class="ab_indent">
                "In these four <em>yaθā ahū vairiiō</em>, at the first <em>š́iiaoθananąm</em> he should turn (the <em>hāwan</em>)."</ab>
<ab>The instruction is rather to be compare with the instruction for the four Ahuna Vairiia of Y27.3.</ab>
        </Quotations>
    </Ritual>
